<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Am I the only would-be PK that actually liked the PvP switch?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?.">.</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:03 p.m. 14/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Am I the only would-be PK that actually liked the PvP switch?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=282" TARGET=_self>Am I the only would-be PK that actually liked the PvP switch?</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I do not see what's the fuss over pk switches, being a Mudder

<BR>&gt; for years I've seen this pk switch system implemented over
<BR>&gt; numerous Mud and they worked rather well. From what I've read on
<BR>&gt; this board the only major downside of pk switch being raised is
<BR>&gt; that it create a gap between RPers and PKers, but there always
<BR>&gt; have been a gap between RPers and PKers in all the Muds I've
<BR>&gt; seen, and most importantly, I think this pk switch actually
<BR>&gt; mends that gap. Ask any RPers why they hate PKers and most of
<BR>&gt; the times it is due to situation like in Ultima Online where
<BR>&gt; innocent RPers are being slaughtered around every corner, pk
<BR>&gt; switch lessen that tension and make it possible for friendship
<BR>&gt; between PKers and RPers(since RPers don't have to worry about
<BR>&gt; getting stabbed in the back).
<BR>&gt; Another reason I like pk switch is that it filters out the 12yrs
<BR>&gt; old KeWlDoOdZ that only have one strategy which is killing
<BR>&gt; innocent newbies. These pk-wannabes have no real skill and
<BR>&gt; generally gets their ass whooped by real pkers. Because of the
<BR>&gt; pk switch,I now am personally looking forward to the challenge
<BR>&gt; of real pkers that actually apply strategy and tactics in EQ
<BR>&gt; because afterall, killing idiots is not all that exciting.
<P>&gt; -heh just realized that I used the word 'pk' instead of PvP in
<BR>&gt; all this post, sorry using mud terms too lazy to change. ;)
<BR>.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
